{"parse":{"title":"List of criminal competencies","pageid":14958343,"revid":789691789,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>List of criminal competencies</b> is a listing of the various types of competencies relevant to the defendant in <a href=\"/wiki/Criminal_law\" title=\"Criminal law\">criminal law</a> in the  <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">United States</a>. In the U.S. the  law is permeated with competency issues since a state may not subject an individual who is \"incompetent\" to trial on criminal charges. In insisting on this requirement the law is acting on the premise that society recognizes only the actions of an autonomous individual. This is a list of the most relevant competencies that must be evaluated (if a question of incompetency is raised) in order to proceed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-melton1997_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-melton1997-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criminal_Competencies\">Criminal Competencies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_criminal_competencies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Criminal Competencies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Competency to Consent to a Search or Seizure - <a href=\"/wiki/Fourth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution\" title=\"Fourth Amendment to the United States Constitution\">Fourth Amendment</a> (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Mapp_v._Ohio\" title=\"Mapp v. Ohio\">Mapp v. Ohio</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Katz_v._United_States\" title=\"Katz v. United States\">Katz v. United States</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Florida_v._Rodriguez\" title=\"Florida v. Rodriguez\">Florida v. Rodriguez</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Stand Trial -  (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Dusky_v._United_States\" title=\"Dusky v. United States\">Dusky v. United States</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Waive Right to Competency -  (<i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=United_States_v._Morin&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"United States v. Morin (page does not exist)\">United States v. Morin</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Confess - (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Brown_v._Mississippi\" title=\"Brown v. Mississippi\">Brown v. Mississippi</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Miranda_v._Arizona\" title=\"Miranda v. Arizona\">Miranda v. Arizona</a></i>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Colorado_v._Connelly\" title=\"Colorado v. Connelly\">Colorado v. Connelly</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Plead Guilty - (<i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Seiling_v._Eyman&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Seiling v. Eyman (page does not exist)\">Seiling v. Eyman</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Godinez_v._Moran\" title=\"Godinez v. Moran\">Godinez v. Moran</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Waive the Right to Counsel - (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Godinez_v._Moran\" title=\"Godinez v. Moran\">Godinez v. Moran</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/McKaskle_v._Wiggins\" title=\"McKaskle v. Wiggins\">McKaskle v. Wiggins</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Faretta_v._California\" title=\"Faretta v. California\">Faretta v. California</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Refuse an Insanity Defense  - (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Frendak_v._United_States\" title=\"Frendak v. United States\">Frendak v. United States</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Testify\n<ul><li>Legal Requirements for Testimonial Competence - <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Rules_of_Evidence\" title=\"Federal Rules of Evidence\">Federal Rules of Evidence</a>,  Rule 601</li>\n<li>Assessment of Witness Credibility - <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Rules_of_Evidence\" title=\"Federal Rules of Evidence\">Federal Rules of Evidence</a>, Rule 508</li></ul></li>\n<li>Competency to Be Sentenced and Executed - (<i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Saddler_v._United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Saddler v. United States (page does not exist)\">Saddler v. United States</a></i>)\n<ul><li>Competency at the Sentencing Proceedings (<i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chavez_v._United_States&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Chavez v. United States (page does not exist)\">Chavez v. United States</a></i>)</li>\n<li>Competency to Be Imprisoned or Executed -  (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Ford_v._Wainwright\" title=\"Ford v. Wainwright\">Ford v. Wainwright</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Penry_v._Lynaugh\" title=\"Penry v. Lynaugh\">Penry v. Lynaugh</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Panetti_v._Quarterman\" title=\"Panetti v. Quarterman\">Panetti v. Quarterman</a></i> )</li></ul></li>\n<li>Competency to Refuse Treatment  - (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Perry_v._Louisiana\" title=\"Perry v. Louisiana\">Perry v. Louisiana</a></i>)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_criminal_competencies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Competency_evaluation_(law)\" title=\"Competency evaluation (law)\">Competency evaluation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Adjudicative_competence\" title=\"Adjudicative competence\">Adjudicative competence</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Footnotes\">Footnotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_criminal_competencies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Footnotes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-melton1997-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-melton1997_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Melton, Gary (1997). <i>Psychological Evaluations for the Courts: A Handbook for Mental Health Professionals and Lawyers</i> (2nd ed.). New York: The Guilford Press. pp.&#160;119&#8211;185. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-57230-236-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-57230-236-4\">1-57230-236-4</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Psychological+Evaluations+for+the+Courts%3A+A+Handbook+for+Mental+Health+Professionals+and+Lawyers&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=119-185&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=The+Guilford+Press&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.isbn=1-57230-236-4&amp;rft.aulast=Melton&amp;rft.aufirst=Gary&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AList+of+criminal+competencies\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1268\nCached time: 20180907230026\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.060 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.076 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 138/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1997/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 93/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1231/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.022/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.34 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   59.791      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   59.791      1 -total\n 81.88%   48.959      1 Template:Cite_book\n  3.39%    2.027      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:14958343-0!canonical and timestamp 20180907230025 and revision id 789691789\n -->\n</div